# ## ðŸŽ‰ What's New in v0.5.12

- **ðŸŽ¨ Enhanced Font Handling**: Improved font property system with more flexible type support and simplified FontManager API
- **ðŸ“¦ Streamlined FontManager**: Simplified `get_font()` method with single parameter design for better usability
- **ðŸ”§ Improved Panel Mixins**: Enhanced `WithBoarder` mixin with automatic `slots_on_paint` initialization for better reliability
- **âš¡ Flexible Type Support**: Added tuple support to font properties alongside existing string and Font object support
- **ðŸ› ï¸ Better Integration**: Removed restrictive type checking from UIAttributes font properties for improved compatibility
- **ðŸ“ Robust Border Drawing**: Automatic paint slot initialization ensures consistent border rendering across all scenarios

### Previous in v0.5.11

- **ðŸ”§ Fixed MutableListView Virtual Scroll Sizing**: Resolved critical issue where scroll bars didn't appear before mainloop execution
- **ðŸ“ Dynamic Virtual Size Updates**: Added automatic `SetVirtualSize(self.sizer.GetMinSize())` calls after append and remove operations
- **âš¡ Immediate Scroll Visibility**: Scroll bars now properly display based on content size without requiring UI refresh cycles
- **ðŸŽ¯ Enhanced User Experience**: Users can now see scroll indicators immediately upon adding content to MutableListView
- **ðŸ› ï¸ Robust Scroll Management**: Proper virtual size calculation ensures consistent scrolling behavior across all scenarios

### Previous in v0.5.10

- **ðŸ”„ Enhanced MutableListView Scroll Handling**: Fixed scroll update issues when adding or removing elements from MutableListView components
- **âš¡ Improved Layout Refresh**: Added automatic layout refresh (`self.layout()`) after append and remove operations for better UI responsiveness
- **ðŸ› ï¸ Fixed Scroll Rate Configuration**: Corrected scroll rate setting method in ScrolledWindow with proper tuple unpacking
- **ðŸŽ¯ Better Component Integration**: Enhanced MutableListView to use BoxSizer consistently for improved layout management
- **ðŸ“± Responsive UI Updates**: Ensured proper scroll bar updates and content positioning during dynamic list modifications

